USER TREES
----------

See au_test/au_ITS.trees for trees with branch lengths.

Tree      logL    deltaL  bp-RELL    p-KH     p-SH       c-ELW       p-AU
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
  1 -4064.131706       0       1 +      1 +      1 +         1 +        1 + 
  2 -4214.086835  149.96       0 - 0.0001 - 0.0001 -  8.92e-17 - 2.13e-63 - 

deltaL  : logL difference from the maximal logl in the set.
bp-RELL : bootstrap proportion using RELL method (Kishino et al. 1990).
p-KH    : p-value of one sided Kishino-Hasegawa test (1989).
p-SH    : p-value of Shimodaira-Hasegawa test (2000).
c-ELW   : Expected Likelihood Weight (Strimmer & Rambaut 2002).
p-AU    : p-value of approximately unbiased (AU) test (Shimodaira, 2002).

Plus signs denote the 95% confidence sets.
Minus signs denote significant exclusion.
All tests performed 10000 resamplings using the RELL method.

ALISIM COMMAND
--------------
To simulate an alignment of the same length as the original alignment, using the tree and model parameters estimated from this analysis, you can use the following command:

--alisim simulated_MSA -t au_test/au_ITS.treefile -m "TN{3.19162,5.4969}+F{0.205218,0.287623,0.291543,0.215616}+R2{0.809521,0.460171,0.190479,3.29424}" --length 788

To mimic the alignment used to produce this analysis, i.e. simulate an alignment of the same length as the original alignment, using the tree and model parameters estimated from this analysis *and* copying the same gap positions as the original alignment, you can use the following command:

iqtree -s au_test/begonia_ITS_shared.fasta --alisim mimicked_MSA

To simulate any number of alignments in either of the two commandlines above, use the --num-alignments options, for example mimic 100 alignments you would use the command line:

iqtree -s au_test/begonia_ITS_shared.fasta --alisim mimicked_MSA --num-alignments 100

For more information on using AliSim, please visit: www.iqtree.org/doc/AliSim

